#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:1
msgid "Rustup for managing Rust versions"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: various](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-various-brightgreen.svg) (this tool has its own "
"versioning scheme and works with all Rust versions)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:5
msgid ""
"The [Rustup](https://rustup.rs/) tool has become _the_ recommended way to "
"install Rust, and is advertised on our website. Its powers go further than "
"that though, allowing you to manage various versions, components, and "
"platforms."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:10
msgid "For installing Rust"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:12
msgid ""
"To install Rust through Rustup, you can go to <https://www.rust-lang.org/"
"install.html>, which will let you know how to do so on your platform. This "
"will install both `rustup` itself and the `stable` version of `rustc` and "
"`cargo`."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:17
msgid ""
"To install a specific Rust version, you can use `rustup toolchain install`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:23
msgid "This works for a specific nightly, as well:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:29
msgid "As well as any of our release channels:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:37
msgid "For updating your installation"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:39
msgid "To update all of the various channels you may have installed:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/rustup-for-managing-rust-versions.md:45
msgid ""
"This will look at everything you've installed, and if there are new "
"releases, will update anything that has one."
msgstr ""

